In this section, we conduct a series of experiments to explore why such a simple gating mechanism can yield significant improvements in performance and training stability. Here are the takeaways according to our analysis: (1) Gating operations enhancing non-linearity consistently lead to performance gains (Sec 4.1); (2) The most effective SDPA elementwise G 1 gate introduces strong input-dependent sparsity to the SDPA outputs (Sec 4.2), which then helps to eliminate the 'attention sink' phenomenon.


